jolt /dʒəʊlt/

(jolting,jolted,jolts) 

1. V-T/V-I If something jolts or if something jolts it, it moves suddenly and quite violently. 使颠簸; 颠簸 

例： The wagon jolted again. 马车又颠簸起来。 

例： The train jolted into motion. 火车颠了一下开动了。 

2. N-COUNT Jolt is also a noun. 颠簸 

例： We were worried that one tiny jolt could worsen her injuries. 我们担心一次轻微的颠簸都可能加剧她的伤情。 

3. V-T If something jolts someone, it gives them an unpleasant surprise or shock. 震惊 

例： A stinging slap across the face jolted her. 火辣辣的一记巴掌使她惊呆了。 

4. N-COUNT Jolt is also a noun. 震惊 

例： Then my husband left me. It gave me the jolt I needed. 后来我的丈夫离开了我。这给了我那个我需要的震动。

